I_3 &= \frac{1}{3} m \times 5^2 = \frac{1}{3} m \times 25 = \frac{25}{3}m.
\end{align*}

Since $3m > \frac{16}{3}m > \frac{25}{3}m$, we have:

\[
I_1 > I_2 > I_3
\]

Thus, the moments of inertia satisfy the inequality $I_1 > I_2 > I_3$ as required.

